verbose_text: Compared with nondiabetic patients, patients with DM were older (66.2 +/- 9.9 vs. 64.1 +/- 12.2 years; P = 0.02) and more likely to be female (31.8 vs. 21.7%; P < 0.01), hypertensive (63.6 vs. 45.2%; P < 0.01), have significant renal impairment as defined by serum creatinine level> = 2 times the upper limit of normal (14.1 vs. 5.1%; P < 0.01), and on statin (78.8 vs. 71.1%; P = 0.04).
